[Noting I got a PM request to take a look]

This ispoorly executed?

[+]Weaknesses

–block


Uh, I hope you don't take this as me dunking on your SCP here: I'm trying to illustrate a whole bunch of stuff which doesn't work for me and by extension how it could be improved.

The ConProcs feel a little overwritten: they're mostly good ideas but there's a few details that might be best left assumed, e.g, the armed guards and the socialisation for good behaviour aspects1? I think the note about the lights being changed so they don't emit UV can also be implied from the mention of them not being exposed to UV?

The Description is worse for this: you have 9 paragraphs of text just explaining what the anomaly is before you even kick off the story and it's too much. It's generally boring to read, and it feels like there's perhaps a few too many anomalous things kicking about that don't have much importance (e.g, the bit where it turns stuff into 5 dimensional things; the secondary anomalous properties of the -3 instance; the plants as well: they feel symbolically important perhaps but they're over-mentioned and I don't quite get the symbolism).

Also, while you can get away with referring to subinstances (e.g, SCP-5536-2) in the ConProcs without defining them, you really should define what they are before mentioning what they do.

After this, there's a really large section about how this was discovered to kick the story off and it'stechnically fine? I feel like 5 pretty big paragraphs about what exactly happened to all the tourists around the SCP is a bit excessive and I'd really suggest trimming it down.

The Observation logs feel unnecessary: they basically just reveal what the description already told us about the dreams, without adding any extra detail other than that the generic  but that info is already hinted towards by the big focus on what happens during both of them in the ConProcs/Description?

The Testing logs also feel a little unnecessary: there's some cool stuff mentioned in them but they don't feelhugely important? At the end of the day, this is largely a story about extradimensional beings with a portal, and the testing logs mostly reinforce that the portal is dangerous to observe?

I'm gonna take a quick formatting thing here: the yellow you use e.g, in [DATA EXPUNGED], and the blue you use in  but you also have the option to use different font styling as shown in the colour blind accessible variant of it).

Uh, everything after the end of the testing logs is generally pretty good and it's very much the strongest aspect of the SCP: unfortunately, you've buried it under a lot of cruft that's not very interesting. The main problem with that is that I really don't have a feel for the stakes here? It feels like this is a thing where I should be acutely aware that the world is being balanced on a knife-edge because of, but instead it feelsabstract and not quite tangible enough?

The writing is super-patchy too: there's a lot of weird phrasings and iffy grammar and I really did attempt a line-by-line but it took me ages and I don't feel like that's the biggest issue here.

Uh, I ended up downvoting this largely because while the core idea is good, the overall display is justfilled with too much stuff that didn't work for me, and the good doesn't feel good enough to overcome that :(




Footnotes
1. Well, I'd keep that second but I'd heavily trim it down








